Yes, the city councils have decided.
Schiltach has to take in 220,000 euros for this.
Deutsche Bahn plans to improve the Kinzigtal railway line next year.
In particular, the safety at railway crossings is to be increased - there are regular collisions of trains with other vehicles across the country.
If the municipalities agree to the restructuring measures, they must participate in the costs with a third, the rest is shared by railways and the federal government.
Schiltach's city builder Roland Griesshaber explained to the municipal council the peculiarities of the Bah crossing "Am Hirschen".
There, the city plans to build a bulge at the level of the tunnel mouth west of the railway tracks.
There, even larger vehicles, such as those that transport long logs, could stand in counter-traffic without having to block the tracks.
Grießhaber therefore proposed to construct a necessary retaining wall in such a way that the city could, in due course, widen the adjacent road in order to ensure a smooth flow of traffic.
