What happens to my email on the way?
E-mail is actually an electronic letter.
Was the drafting of the Internet service e-mail technically implemented as in the case of the conventional postal service?
In the conception of the early Internet services, the focus was on making communication possible.
Therefore, in the basic technical protocols, attention has not been paid to creating a stable foundation for a sound exchange of letters.
Therefore, a traditional email corresponds more to an open postcard than to a sealed letter.
When user "Anna" sends an email to "Benni", are the computers of the two directly connected?
In the first step, Anna’s e-mail program or browser sends the e-mail to the mail server of its service provider.
For example, if she has a GMail account, that would be Google.
This mail server sends the content to the provider that Benni uses.
On the way, the mail can run over a number of other servers on the Internet.
Bennie can then call the content to his provider.
Are traditional e-mails read along their way through the network?
Most emails are read several times by software robots on the way.
The sender's provider usually checks whether the mail contains a malicious program as an attachment.
A virus check is also carried out on the receiver systems.
In addition, the providers check whether it is an annoying and unwanted spam email that is immediately deleted or at least sorted away in a spam folder.
Do robots have another task?
In systems like GMail, the robot also determines the information Google needs to place context advertising.
When Anna and Benni communicate via GMail about their upcoming holiday trip, Google can display corresponding links to holiday offers.
Do unknown people also read emails?
The likelihood of unauthorized people reading an email is extremely low.
In theory, however, this is possible.
In companies, administrators often have the opportunity to read electronic mail.
Law enforcement agencies and intelligence agencies also have legal options to intercept or take note of emails.
In addition, there are possible illegal spying actions.
Is it possible to protect e-mails from reading along?
With an encryption according to the OpenPGP standard, an e-mail can be encrypted effectively against co-reading.
With high technical effort, it is also possible to conceal the metadata of an e-mail communication, so that it is not even easy to recognize who has communicated with whom.
How important are Yahoo and Google in the email market in Germany?
According to a survey conducted by Convios Consulting in August 2013, Yahoo and Google play only a minor role in the main privately used mailboxes.
